  "texts": [
    "Perhaps most importantly, our model improvement analysis suggests that as LLMs enhance their context-understanding capabilities, this disparity may persist or even widen.",
    "Rather than narrowing the gap between capability and iterative innovation, improved LLMs appear to disproportionately enhance iterative innovation, potentially reshaping innovation trajectories in collaborative environments.",
    "This suggests that the self-selection mechanism in voluntary collaborative settings may increasingly direct contributors toward iterative innovation as LLMs make these tasks more efficient, potentially requiring deliberate interventions to maintain a healthy balance of innovation types.",
    "These patterns likely extend beyond software development to other knowledge domains where LLMs are being deployed.",
    "Tasks that benefit from detailed context and have clear evaluation criteria-such as analyzing customer service issues based on past similar cases, verifying data accuracy against established rules, or retrieving relevant documents from large collections-may see disproportionate benefits from LLMs compared to tasks requiring novel conceptualization without clear precedent."
